This article is a statement made by the President on the International Day in Support of Victims of Torture. The President emphasizes the importance of eradicating torture and all forms of cruel treatment or punishment around the world. He states that torture goes against the values of the United States and undermines national security. The President affirms that the United States legally prohibits torture and that all U.S. personnel are prohibited from engaging in torture. He also mentions the efforts made to confront the past, including ending the CIA's detention and interrogation program and supporting the declassification of key details. The President acknowledges that torture is still prevalent in the world and emphasizes the need for the United States to continue playing a leading role in eradicating it and supporting torture victims. He salutes those working to end torture and thanks them for upholding the commitment to human dignity.